<br>
As far as being the main tank goes, steering the mob is key.  You have to keep mobs (especially the AOE ones) away from the casters.  Also, try to give the other melee room...arrange it so that you are the only one attacking the mob from the front and have everyone else (rogue or not) attack from the back.  This way, they will be able to avoid ripostes, dodges, parries, etc and also enrage...not to mention you do more damage when attacking from the back.  If you find the mob getting pushed by all the melee from the back, just turn the mob (and let the raid know when you do so so that they will be prepared to change position).  It takes a lot of practice and I think every tank does HoT differently, but this is what I've learned works best. <p><p align="center"><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104582"><IMG SRC="http://members.aol.com/tinvic/sig4.jpg"></A><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104582">Magelo's profile of my corpse</a> 
