<br>
HoT is...easy.<br>
<br>
Spoiler guide of HoT ahead. Dont want it, dont read.<br>
Add any info I screwed up on, or forgot out, its late here and I'm tired  <br>
<br>
1 GOOD group with what I call adverage gear (epics or there abouts, semi rare stuff cof etc, good quest items like 9th ring, etc) is all you need. And yes, maybe what ive listed is above every day joeblow's gear, but most of that stuff is 1 group obtainable, or even by a small guild. 18 people or LESS.<br>
1 good group consisting of:<br>
cleric, rogue, Warrior, ench, shaman, bard.<br>
can do this area easily. I 2box the ench so hes usually sitting out, and we have a monk or another melee in place of the ench.<br>
<br>
anyways, if you can split the first two mobs, you can pillage the zone. a 60 can ALMOST allways split the first 2 WITHOUT FD. Dont say it cant be done, I do it every time we go  <br>
<br>
As main tank 99.9% of the time in HoT, I never use resist gear beyond whats on my gear (see profile on sig). The added AC/HP I would loose by getting 230+ resists w/druid just dont add up to the pure melee damage I take. It makes Complete heal more effective, etc.<br>
<br>
PLEASE, if I'm wrong on any of the following correct me, I'm doing this without looking at my logs, and off the top of my head, so some (but I doubt much) may be wrong.<br>
Any added parses of adverage life, or damage per swing while defensive or not welcome  <br>
<br>
Mob ~HPs are just estimate off the top of my head based on how long 1 group takes to kill them, so dont be suprised if I'm 5 or even 10k high or low. sorry  <br>
<br>
~~~~~~<br>
Mobs:<br>
<br>
Wurms: generally 2 Types of them, White and Red.<br>
Red: Burning and Fiery. Fiery has a 400~ AE, fire based. Burning has Two types, the same as fiery (400~) and a LESS resistable Burning ae for 550~.<br>
White: Ancient and Guardian (?). AFAIK the only difference I see is ancient is arguable tougher, higher level, more ac, more hp, and more mana.<br>
Wurms have roughly it seems a 40% drop rate, and sometimes dropping up to 2, or 3 pieces at a time (Saw 2 plate BP's 1 silk robe on one before!!)<br>
Anyone Parsed Estimate HP? I'm saying about ~30K? maybe more.<br>
<br>
all hit for about Tripple/Quad 550 w/o defensive. ~330 defensive.<br>
Obvious resists are Fire for white wurms, and cold for fire wurms. RARELY slowable with just tash. Need Mala(o) Tash atleast to get it off without SEVERE Luck.<br>
<br>
Wyverns: 3 general types. Vhements Raging and I'm gapping out on the 3rd kind.<br>
Relativly easy, I tank these without defensive and about 5600hp fully buffed. All are medium difficulty slowable BUT the Vhement. Tash + slow can usually stick. Need malo tash occlusion to MEDIUM difficulty slow the Vhements.<br>
Vhements Quad for ~350 VERY fast, Id estimate 15 to 18 delay. Others double to quad for ~280.<br>
drop rates are meh on them, maybe 1 in 6 or so, 1 in 8 more likely. Usually SK mobs, HT, and usuall SK spells.<br>
Estimated HP? meh, ~18k+ no more then 25<br>
I defensive on the Vhements, rest are a waiste.<br>
<br>
Drakes: Lots of types. Red, Blue (2 kinds?), Black, Brown, Green.<br>
<br>
Red: Fire ae for ~100? doubles for 250 or so, easy. Slowable with Tash, occlusion.<br>
Blue: I believe there is 2 kinds, A cleric type mob with a damage ae, and a stupid one with a mana DOT. annoying at best. Maybe they are just 1 type with a varying ae, I forget  <br>
Black: Shadow Knight mob, HT's for 900+ based on his level. Usually just melees while casting annoying Debuffs. Has a &quot;Acid Jet&quot; DOT, Magic based. something like 2000 damage in 400 ticks. Annoying at best.<br>
Brown: Shimmering Drakes or some such. Druid mob? huge DS on these, can cast root, gate, and DOT's.<br>
Green: My personal favorite. AE Slow. forget the name, &quot;You have been covered in Slime&quot; or some such. lasts about ~15 min. REALLY annoying mobs  I Dont defensive on any of these.<br>
~15-25k? hp<br>
<br>
and last but not least, The Rancars. 3 or 4 types. from plain &quot;A rancar&quot; up to the more difficult &quot;An ancient Rancar&quot; or some such<br>
Easy. Nuff said. None of them are hard imo. I dont use defensive on these.<br>
~15k? life<br>
<br>
any NAMED mob.<br>
Drake form, NO AE, NO casters, PURE melee.<br>
hits for ~550 quad, without defensive. ~380 ish with? forget  <br>
about same difficulty as wurms IMO, maybe a bit more HP.<br>
Id say ~30-45k? its been a while since we ganked any.<br>
~~~~~~~<br>
<br>
All static/Roamers repop in ~80 min.<br>
Named Drakes are 3 days.<br>
Doezekar is 1 week, no randomizer (Thanks farmability, /rude verant)<br>
<br>
Again, my apologies for any info thats wrong, i'm tired, and not on my comp with logs to look at the real crap (thx holidays), so any real logs are welcome.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps! <br>
<br>
